    "description": {
      "value": "\n      <div topic='Gem of Brightness' level='8'><p><b>Gem of Brightness:</b> This crystal appears to be a long, rough prism. Upon utterance of a command word, the crystal emits bright light of one of three sorts.</p><ul>\n <li> One command word causes the gem to shed light as a hooded lantern. This use of the gem does not expend any charges.</li>\n <li> Another command word causes the <i>gem of brightness</i> to send out a bright ray 1 foot in diameter and 50 feet long. This strikes as a ranged touch attack, and any creature struck by this beam is blinded for 1d4 rounds unless it makes a DC 14 Fortitude save. This use of the gem expends 1 charge.</li>\n <li> The third command word causes the gem to flare in a blinding flash of light that fills a 30-foot cone. Although this glare lasts but a moment, any creature within the cone must make a DC 14 Fortitude save or be blinded for 1d4 rounds. This use expends 5 charges.</li>\n</ul><p>A newly created <i>gem of brightness</i> has 50 charges. When all its charges are expended, the gem becomes nonmagical.</p><p>Faint evocation; CL 6th; Craft Wondrous Item, <i>daylight</i>; Price 13,000 gp.</p>\n</div>\n    ",
